reviews.review_text: The Best To My Ears I've listened to most of the versions of this show on here, and this, to my ears, is the best. Like the others, the sound takes a while to settle in, what with the balloon drop and subsequent popping which runs throughout the opener, but by Scarlet>Fire it's settled in nicely, and what a Scarlet>Fire. This is an essential show, and as always, any show with the Miller and/or Gastwirt names attached is worth the DL.
